Business Intelligence Developer
Employment Type: Temporary Full Time (11 months)
Position Classification: Health Manager Level 4
Remuneration: $147,653 - $175,917, plus Superannuation

Join our Information Management and Quality team at Ministry of Health for an exciting temporary employment opportunity and be part of the team enriching health in millions of ways every day.  

About us 

We are committed to your growth and development, providing the resources and opportunities you need to excel in your career.
Our core values of collaboration, openness, respect, and empowerment are more than just words – they're the guiding principles that shape every aspect of our work.
Join a passionate team dedicated to innovation and creativity.

To learn more about the Ministry and what benefits we offer, access our Employee Benefits Handbook.

About the role
With your skills and experience, you can contribute to the millions of ways we’re enhancing health and wellness while developing your career as part of the largest health organisation in Australia. 

Health Manager level 4 starting salary from $147,653 - $175,917plus Super, with a 38- hour work week.

What you’ll be doing

Collaborate with stakeholders to understand business processes and translate them into data requirements.
Lead the design and development of data models and data marts to support efficient reporting and analysis.
Manage ETL processes to ensure accurate, secure, and timely data integration from multiple sources.
Monitor and optimise BI solution performance, ensuring fast and reliable data access.
Stay current with BI technologies and propose enhancements to improve solution effectiveness.

About you
We are seeking motivated and committed individuals who can support the work of NSW Health with:

You hold a degree or diploma in Information Technology (or equivalent experience).
You have strong knowledge of data warehousing, dimensional modelling, and performance tuning using T-SQL and execution plans.
You bring hands-on experience with SSIS, SQL Server (2012+), and source control tools like GIT.
You’re comfortable working in Agile and DevOps environments, with exposure to Microsoft Azure and Power BI.
You’re a strong communicator and problem-solver, capable of working independently or as part of a team.

How to apply
At The Ministry of Health, we want you to make the most of the opportunities you’ll get to grow your skills and your career, surrounded by authentic, smart people and leaders.

Please review the role description and submit your up-to-date resume (up to 5 pages) and cover letter (1-2 pages) and explaining your interest and motivation in applying for this role and highlighting your relevant skills.

For role related queries or questions contact Harkanwal Singh on harkanwal.singh@health.nsw.gov.au and quote REQ618760

If you do require any adjustments to the recruitment process during the recruitment process, please contact Lisa Byrne on lisa.byrne@health.nsw.gov.au

Applications Close: Friday 21 November 2025 (11:59PM)

Our client, providing operational and infrastructure assessment and optimisation services to the Queensland resources sector, is seeking a Capacity Modeller to join their close-knit team. Integral to the role is delivering simulation and supply chain modelling, providing insights and working closely with internal and external stakeholders.


Reporting to the Capacity Modelling Manager, key responsibilities include

Collate and input stakeholder data into discrete event simulation modelling tools to assess the capacity of the supply chain network and infrastructure.
Critically analyse and challenge modelling outcomes, drawing conclusions and predicting future outcomes.
Provide recommendations, insights and implications of real-world operations and impacts.
Identify data and modelling issues and provide solutions.
Create value and contribute to operational process improvements.
Proactively communicate and work closely with the CEO, Modelling & Reporting Teams and external operational customers.
  
About you

Practitioner of capacity, planning and simulation modelling within a supply chain, transport, mining, manufacturing or consulting environment.
Experience using discrete event simulation modelling tools such as Anylogic, ExtendSim, Arena or similar.
Relevant tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Mathematics, Software Engineering, IT, Supply Chain/ Logistics or a related discipline.
The ability to build and maintain key stakeholder relationships and link customer needs to solutions.
A curious mind with strong analytical and problem-solving skills, coupled with excellent communication and storytelling abilities.
  
On offer

A competitive salary package including a performance-related bonus.
Flexible hybrid work arrangements.
The opportunity to work alongside highly experienced industry experts who are driven to provide exceptional support to their valued customers.
Work on complex, multi-stakeholder projects with the ability to drive improvements and change.
Be part of a proactive company that embraces innovation and actively pursues modern technologies and digital solutions
  
To apply, please send your latest resume and cover letter in Word format to Onten Strategic Recruitment. For an initial confidential discussion, please contact Michelle Gray or Sarah Armstrong on +61 7 3519 5810. 
  
All third-party and unsolicited resumes will be forwarded to Onten for an independent assessment.
